{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":12484,"name":"","username":"kaapa","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/k/f0a364/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-06-12T20:22:38.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHello,\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI am pretty new to Urho3D. As a side project, I‚Äôve decided to make a simple rubik‚Äôs cube game. Everything works fine, except that I can‚Äôt get the texturing right. Basically, what I want to achieve is to have just one model, which will represent a single cubie which will be colored differently based on to which cube face it belongs. My problem is that, I don‚Äôt know where to start. The documentation of materials tells me nothing. The one interesting thing I found was Cubemap, which to my understanding, will provide me with the ability to set different texture to different faces of the model. But, when using cubemap (I set all cubemap faces to be red), my whole cube went completely black.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTo sum up:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eI want to have just one model.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eI want to set different colors to different cube faces.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnd I completely don‚Äôt know how to do that, or even search for info/examples on how to do it. Do you guys know how to do it? Do you have any examples of something like this working?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhat I‚Äôve done is this\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ematerial - rubiks.xml\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[code]\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[/code]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003etexture - rubiks.xml\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\u0026lt;cubemap\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;face name=\"red.png\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;face name=\"red.png\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;face name=\"red.png\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;face name=\"red.png\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;face name=\"red.png\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;face name=\"red.png\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;quality low=\"0\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/cubemap\u0026gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhere red.png is just 16x16 png image.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThanks,\u003cbr\u003e\nKacper\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:12:49.882Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":151,"reads":23,"readers_count":22,"score":759.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":2074,"topic_slug":"rubiks-cube-texturing-adding-material-cubemap","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":487,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":12491,"name":"È≠îÂ§ßÂÜú ùûçùûéùù≥ ÁèæÊãõËúç","username":"Modanung","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/{size}/3290_2.png","created_at":"2016-06-13T11:53:18.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eA cubemap is not what you‚Äôre looking for. Those are used for reflections and backgrounds.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://luckeyproductions.nl/mdl/RubixCubie.mdl\" data-bbcode=\"true\"\u003eThis model\u003c/a\u003e \u003ca href=\"http://luckeyproductions.nl/blends/RubixCubie.blend\" data-bbcode=\"true\"\u003e[Blend]\u003c/a\u003e uses vertex colors. Applying a material with a VCol technique will show the colors.\u003cbr\u003e\nThere‚Äôs a lot of ways you could do this, but I think this is the most straightforward one.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI know it‚Äôs better to teach a person how to fish than to give one a fish. But I think this is more like providing a hook. \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=5\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:12:50.367Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":20,"readers_count":19,"score":14.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":2074,"topic_slug":"rubiks-cube-texturing-adding-material-cubemap","display_username":"È≠îÂ§ßÂÜú ùûçùûéùù≥ ÁèæÊãõËúç","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://luckeyproductions.nl/mdl/RubixCubie.mdl","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":15},{"url":"http://luckeyproductions.nl/blends/RubixCubie.blend","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":12}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":192,"hidden":false,"trust_level":0,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_suspended":true,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":12494,"name":"","username":"kaapa","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/k/f0a364/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-06-13T15:46:20.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003egreat, thanks for help!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMeanwhile I‚Äôve figured out that I can make a blender cube model which will have 6 different materials (one per side), and then just use SetMaterial method (with proper material index as a first argument) to set different colored materials. Is it going to work?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThanks,\u003cbr\u003e\nKacper\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:12:50.590Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":20,"readers_count":19,"score":24.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":2074,"topic_slug":"rubiks-cube-texturing-adding-material-cubemap","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":487,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":12495,"name":"","username":"1vanK","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/1vank/{size}/768_2.png","created_at":"2016-06-13T16:43:25.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eWhy do you need 6 materials? Just unwrap cube model and paint texture with 6 colored rectangles.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:12:50.651Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":20,"readers_count":19,"score":9.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":2074,"topic_slug":"rubiks-cube-texturing-adding-material-cubemap","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":true,"admin":false,"staff":true,"user_id":263,"hidden":false,"trust_level":4,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":12496,"name":"È≠îÂ§ßÂÜú ùûçùûéùù≥ ÁèæÊãõËúç","username":"Modanung","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/{size}/3290_2.png","created_at":"2016-06-13T16:53:57.000Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"kaapa\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/k/f0a364/40.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e kaapa:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMeanwhile I‚Äôve figured out that I can make a blender cube model which will have 6 different materials (one per side), and then just use SetMaterial method (with proper material index as a first argument) to set different colored materials. Is it going to work?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYes, that would be another way. Mind you that for the Geometry indices to match the material order in Blender you usually need to \u003ca href=\"https://www.blender.org/manual/modeling/meshes/editing/misc.html\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003esort the elements\u003c/a\u003e by material.\u003cbr\u003e\nEight months ago CodeMonkey provided this image to help me find it:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"http://savepic.su/6184007.png\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"http://savepic.su/6184007m.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn case you need to do this for many objects in the future, this python script will do the same for all selected objects:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[code]\u003cbr\u003e\nimport bpy\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003efor ob in bpy.context.selected_objects:\u003cbr\u003e\nbpy.context.scene.objects.active = ob\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003ebpy.ops.object.mode_set(mode = 'EDIT')\nbpy.ops.mesh.select_all(action='SELECT')\nbpy.ops.mesh.sort_elements(type='MATERIAL', elements={'FACE'})\nbpy.ops.object.mode_set(mode = 'OBJECT')[/code]\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFor assigning the materials (in C++11) you‚Äôre probably best of using something like:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003efor (int i{0}; i \u0026lt; model-\u0026gt;GetNumGeometries(); ++i) {\n\n    Material* material{ GetResource\u0026lt;Material\u0026gt;(path)-\u0026gt;Clone() };\n    switch (i){\n    default:\n    case 0: material-\u0026gt;SetShaderParameter(\"MatDiffColor\", Color::WHITE);\n    break;\n    case 1: material-\u0026gt;SetShaderParameter(\"MatDiffColor\", Color::RED);\n    break;\n    ...\n    }\n    model-\u0026gt;SetMaterial(i, material);\n}\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThat way you don‚Äôt have to create and edit six materials and the glossiness or technique can be changed by editing this one material. Cloning the materials once for the entire cube would be more efficient though.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:12:50.720Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":19,"readers_count":18,"score":58.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":2074,"topic_slug":"rubiks-cube-texturing-adding-material-cubemap","display_username":"È≠îÂ§ßÂÜú ùûçùûéùù≥ ÁèæÊãõËúç","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://savepic.su/6184007.png","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"6184007.png","clicks":6},{"url":"https://www.blender.org/manual/modeling/meshes/editing/misc.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Miscellaneous Editing Tools ‚Äî Blender Manual","clicks":5}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":192,"hidden":false,"trust_level":0,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_suspended":true,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_an